title: Fort Dodge Trisports Rock N Roller Race
Ames Assault Roller Race
description: Iowa Championship Roller Race Event.  Two at time.  No rerides.  Two miles on Kreitler roller with headwind and flywheel, timed by Roller Fusion Program.
course: 2 miles for time on the Kreitler killer headwind rollers w/flywheel.  Timed by Roller Fusion.  If you turn more than 15 inches, you\'ve fallen off the course.
registration: Day of registration only.  Registration closes at 2pm.
notes: All USCF rules apply and helmets are required.
directions: From the south (hwy 69), east or west (hwy 30): go north on Hwy 69/ S Duff to S 3rd St and turn left.  Bike World is on your left in the first block.  From the north (Hwy 69): follow 69S through Ames.  After you turn south onto S Duff take the second right onto S 3rd St.  Bike World is on your left in the first block.

title: Iowa Spring Classic Series 1, Grinnell IA
description: Road Race featuring a combination of road and gravel surfaces.
course: 7.1 mile course  (4 corner CLOCKWISE loop) of flat to rolling terrain; 1.5 miles paved and 5.6 miles gravel. Start/Finish will be outside Rock Creek State Park.
registration: Pre and day of registration is $15. For pre-registration mail a check for $15 with signed and dated USAC entry/release to; Brett Griggs PO Box 784 Iowa City IA 52244, pre-registration ends on 2/27/3010. On site day of registration opens at 7:30AM and closes at 8:40AM. There is no late fee for this race.
notes:
All USAC rules apply and a helmet is required at all times. 

Due to the combination of gravel and road surfaces, riders would be best off using cyclocross bicycles or at least heavy duty tires. There will be no nuetral support, no nuetral wheels, and no neutral follow vehicle. Carry your pump or CO2 cannister during your race.
directions: From Grinnell IA; Take Hwy 6 (West) to Hwy T38N, turn right (North) on Hwy T38N to Co HWY F27, turn left (West) on Co Hwy F27, Rock Creek State Park entrance in approx 1 mile off left (South) side of Co Hwy F27

title: Iowa Spring Classic Series 2, Iowa City IA
description: Road Race featuring a combination of road and gravel surfaces.
course: 6.3 mile course  (4 intersection CLOCKWISE loop) of rolling to hilly terrain; 3.5 miles paved and 3.7 miles gravel. Start/Finish will be 350meters South of the intersection of Bayertown Rd SW & Naples Ave SW.
registration: Pre and day of registration is $15. For pre-registration mail a check for $15 with signed and dated USAC entry/release to; Brett Griggs PO Box 784 Iowa City IA 52244, pre-registration ends on 3/6/3010. On site day of registration opens at 8:30AM and closes at 9:40AM. There is no late fee for this race. None licensed riders are required to buy a one day USAC license to race.
notes:
All USAC rules apply and a helmet is required at all times.
NO REFUNDS, in accordance with USCF rules.  

Due to the combination of gravel and road surfaces, riders would be best off using cyclocross bicycles or at least heavy duty tires. There will be no nuetral support, no nuetral wheels, and no neutral follow vehicle. Carry your pump or CO2 cannister with you during your race.
directions: From Hills IA take Co Rd F62/Oakcrest Hill Rd SE (North) to Co Rd F62/500th St SW, turn left (West) on Co Rd F62/500th St SW, turn left (South) on Naples Ave SW.

title: Iowa Spring Classic Series 3, Colfax IA
Twin Bing Classic Road Race
description: Traing race in the beautiful loess hills of western Iowa.
course: Course starts at regestration area and proceds west of town on county Road D-54, north on D-25  East on D-38 past bronson, and south on K-64 back to climbing Hill. Finish one mile west of town
registration: Regestraion at Woodbury County Sheriff substation. Day of only closes at 10.45 am
notes: Race will consist of an A race and B race A race will consist of cat 1,2,3  B race will be cat 4,5 women, juniors and masters. Masters can race category if they chose.  Yellow line rule will be enforced.  Wheels in, Wheels out. Feedzone in front of start area.
directions: Race starts in Climbing Hill ,Iowa 15 miles SE of Sioux City.  No gas or food available in town.

title: Eagle Point Criterium
description: Presented by Premier Bank.  Race in Dubuque\'s beautiful Eagle Point Park on the bluffs of the Mighty Mississippi.  This is a great event for the entire family.
course: Not your usual four corner course through a business park, the Eagle Point Criterium course is a one mile loop with right and left corners and modest changes in elevation.
registration: Registration on-site, adjacent to the start / finish, is open at 8:00 AM and ends :15 prior to each scheduled race start time.
directions: In  Dubuque, Exit Highway 151 North at Kerper Blvd.  Turn left on Fengler Street, then right on Rhomberg Ave.  Turn left on Shiras Avenue after less than one mile.  Follow local signage to Eagle Point Park.
